    <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/methodological-review-of-the-student-income-and-expenditure-survey"/>
    <title>Methodological review of the student income and expenditure survey</title>
    <content type="html">&lt;div class="govspeak"&gt;&lt;p&gt;BIS research paper no. 29. Report of a review commissioned by BIS. Examines the methods used for the last two student income and expenditure surveys (SIESs) and the feasibility of alternative approaches. Looks at current thinking, knowledge and experience of relevant student finance surveys, makes recommendations for the next planned round of SIES (expected in 2011/12). Focused on sampling and contacting students, response rates, data collection, data linking, and likely implications of any methodological changes on the ability to measure trends over time.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</content>
