    <title>Expanding and improving part-time higher education</title>
    <content type="html">&lt;div class="govspeak"&gt;&lt;p&gt;BIS research paper no. 68. Report on research that explores whether part-time undergraduate study in England can be expanded as an alternative for young students (those aged 22 and under) to the full-time three to four year model of first degree undergraduate participation. Also looks at how undergraduate part-time students of all ages can be encouraged and supported with their studies.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</content>
